Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses wireless networks and their interconnection, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - WSANs are distributed systems, and the paper discusses the challenges of managing QoS in such systems. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses how WSANs enable cyber systems to monitor and manipulate the physical world, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions security as a challenge in WSANs, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper briefly mentions the use of information theory in WSANs, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
